Locked architectural decisions
1. Override is a separate trust artifact

An Override does not modify the original Decision.

It records a human-authorized exception that becomes part of the Execution Trust Record.

2. Override is immutable

Once recorded:

it cannot be edited;
it cannot be deleted;
it becomes part of the permanent audit history.
3. Override occurs before Execution

Based on the locked architecture:

Decision
      │
      ▼
Rejected
      │
      ▼
Override (Optional)
      │
      ▼
Execution

Overrides are not permitted after a terminal Execution (COMPLETED or FAILED).

4. One active Override per Business Transaction

A Business Transaction may have at most one accepted Override.

Additional override attempts are rejected.

The history remains append-only.

5. Parmana records the authority

The client does not supply:

overriddenBy
overriddenAt

These values are populated by Parmana from:

the authenticated identity,
the system clock.

This ensures the integrity of the audit trail.

Canonical Principle (Locked)

An Override records an authorized human exception to an immutable Decision.

It never replaces the original Decision. Instead, it becomes an independent trust artifact that preserves who authorized the exception, when it occurred, and why it was made, maintaining the append-only integrity of the Execution Trust Record.



{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/override.schema.json",
  "title": "Override",
  "description": "Canonical Override artifact for a Business Transaction.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "overrideId",
    "outcome",
    "reason",
    "overriddenBy",
    "overriddenAt"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "overrideId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique Override identifier."
    },
    "outcome": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Override decision outcome.",
      "enum": [
        "APPROVED",
        "REJECTED"
      ]
    },
    "reason": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Business justification for the override.",
      "minLength": 1
    },
    "reference": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional external approval, change request, or ticket reference."
    },
    "overriddenBy": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Authenticated identity that authorized the override."
    },
    "overriddenAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "UTC timestamp when the override was recorded."
    },
    "metadata": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Implementation-specific override metadata.",
      "additionalProperties": true
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "overrideId": "OVR-000001",
      "outcome": "APPROVED",
      "reason": "Regional manager approved the exception.",
      "reference": "CHG-12345",
      "overriddenBy": "manager-001",
      "overriddenAt": "2026-06-26T11:05:00Z",
      "metadata": {
        "department": "Risk Operations"
      }
    }
  ]
}